{
  "stem": "10588.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it should be fat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you know, when the mother went to the butcher, to the kosher butcher, give me a fat piece of meat, you know?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we would buy the, the chickens there and then take them to the ritual slaughterer, which was there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one time my mother asked me to go to the ritual slaughter, to [SPEAKING YIDDISH], which means 'to slaughter the chicken.' And I don't know why she said it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She said, don't tell the chicken that it's going to be killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's [HEBREW], which means-- in Hebrew, it's a sin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You're not allowed to tell any-- you know, like, you have to-- don't inflict pain on the, on the chicken.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was thinking, the chicken will understand my language?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Seemed to me very funny, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also, in connection with the livestock buying from, from the peasants, is my parents used to-- in Poland, a girl needed a dowry.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, since you were little, if you had daughters, you started to make the trousseau for the dowry and everything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I remember, as today, my mother and grandmother sometimes used to sit, and they plucked the, the chicken, or-- so the chicken feathers they always thew away.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when it was a geese or a duck, the down, they would, they would save.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was later for pillows, for down quilts.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And always she used to say, [NON-ENGLISH], which means 'God willing'-- when Itkele-- I was the oldest, and I was the [? firstborn-- ?] she's going to get married, she's going to have nice, you know, pillows, with down and everything else.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whenever they were making [INAUDIBLE], that was always their wish, and that's why I feel so horrible that they didn't live to fulfill that wish.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They should be able to take me under the chuppah, which means under the canopy, when I'm going to get married.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ciechonw was a small town-- as I mentioned, 90 kilometer north of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I looked out through the window, I saw in the morning little boys with payele, with the Hasidic, you know-- going to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People were religious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- it had a [NON-ENGLISH], which means a special-- where there were made loans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Let's say, if somebody was poor and they needed a loan to go in business or to help somebody, people would lend money.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would lend them to those.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, in order not to shame them-- was a prohibition against shaming somebody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not menschlich.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they would know who they were loaning the money, and the other was-- it was anonymous, you know?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Charity giving was supposed to be anonymous.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Speaking of charity, when I was a little girl, I remember, every morning-- because the story of charity reminds me of something of the grandmother that I was planning to tell you.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every morning, when I got up, my grandmother would say with me the prayers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SPEAKING YIDDISH]-- you know, the prayer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And every night, before I went to sleep, she would say with me the prayers again-- the, you know, prayers for thanking God for getting up and for to get up-- you know, special prayers.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For everything, there was a prayer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She would not permit me to take a bite of food without saying, saying a prayer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she used to give me coins.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She had a tin can, which she called the 'pushke.' It was for tzedakah, charity box.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And always to put in coins, to teach me tzedakah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, and she used to-- always, when she gave me, she gave me coins, she used to say that to help others, those who are less fortunate, is a mitzvah, a commandment.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember one time, I was a little girl, still, and a poor man came to our house and asked my grandmother for alms-- for tzedakah.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not-- there was no social security or welfare at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the people used to help the people, you know?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were some people who were poor and used to go to beg.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my grandmother took a few coins, and she gave them to me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she said, Itkele, please give it to the man waiting at the door.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At that time, I was still a little girl.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't know one coin from the other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was always a curious girl.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wanted to know everything, where and why, always asking question.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, my father used to joke with me, Itkele, [SPEAKING YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I always want to know where the [? feet ?] are [? growing ?] from.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words, to know the beginning, the essence, the mysteries.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I looked in, in my hand.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, Grandmother!",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
